sk is suspended. It is possible to immediately resume the task, or escape the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"continuation in order to complete it afterwards, which will then resume the suspended task.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"resume(throwing:)"},{"type":"text","text":" is called on the continuation, this function throws that error."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You must invoke the continuation’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"resume"},{"type":"text","text":" method exactly once."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Missing to invoke it (eventually) will cause the calling task to remain suspended"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"indefinitely which will result in the task “hanging” as well as being leaked with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"no possibility to destroy it."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The checked continuation offers detection of misuse, and dropping the last reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to it, without having resumed it will trigger a warning. Resuming a continuation twice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is also diagnosed and will cause a crash."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"withCheckedContinuation(function:_:)"}]}],"style":"note","name":"See Also","type":"aside"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"withUnsafeContinuation(function:_:)"}]}],"type":"aside","name":"See Also","style":"note"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"withUnsafeThrowingContinuation(function:_:)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","name":"See Also","type":"aside"}]}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths